But I'm going to
approximate it by the slope

00:04:18.241 --> 00:04:19.738
between these two points.

00:04:19.738 --> 00:04:21.080
Between those two points,

00:04:21.080 --> 00:04:24.107
our change in quantity is 2,

00:04:24.107 --> 00:04:28.350
and our change in total revenue is 8.

00:04:28.350 --> 00:04:30.081
Our change in total revenue is 8.

00:04:30.081 --> 00:04:31.926
When we produced 2,

00:04:31.926 --> 00:04:32.995
or 2,000 pounds,

00:04:32.995 --> 00:04:37.711
our total revenue was $8,000.

00:04:37.711 --> 00:04:39.740
So we have a change in total revenue of 8,

00:04:39.740 --> 00:04:41.317
or 8,000, I guess we could say,

00:04:41.317 --> 00:04:45.008
divided by a change in quantity of 2,000,

00:04:45.008 --> 00:04:47.822
so our marginal revenue at this point

00:04:47.822 --> 00:04:50.888
is 8 divided by 2, or
8,000 divided by 2,000,

00:04:50.888 --> 00:04:53.046
which is $4 per pound.

00:04:53.046 --> 00:04:55.065
When our quantity is 1,

00:04:55.065 --> 00:04:59.209
our marginal revenue is $4 per pound.

00:04:59.209 --> 00:05:02.064
It is $4 per pound, just like that.

00:05:02.064 --> 00:05:04.360
Now, let's think about
the marginal revenue

00:05:04.360 --> 00:05:06.708
when our quantity is 2.

00:05:06.708 --> 00:05:07.761
To do that,

00:05:07.761 --> 00:05:09.986
I'm going to find the slope
between these two points.

00:05:09.986 --> 00:05:12.199
We really want to find
the slope of that line,

00:05:12.199 --> 00:05:14.655
but it looks like the slope
between these two points

00:05:14.655 --> 00:05:16.139
